        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 9:21PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 920 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arden, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carlsbad, San Angelo State Park, Arden, The Intersection Of Highway
208 And Ranch Road 2662, O.C. Fisher Reservoir, Water Valley, and
Grape Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
